President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his Administration. These include Kenneth William Staley, who will be the Coordinator of United States Government Activities to Combat Malaria Globally. Dr. Staley has experience in public health crisis responses and has worked in the pharmaceutical and medical device industries. He has also served in various roles during the George W. Bush administration. Other appointments include Deputy Secretary Stephen Censky, Under Secretary for Trade and Foreign Agricultural Affairs Ted McKinney, Under Secretary for Marketing and Regulatory Programs Gregory Ibach, Under Secretary for Foreign Agriculture Services William Northey, and Principal Deputy General Counsel Stephen Vaden, who will all be members of the Commodity Credit Corporation Board of Directors at the Department of Agriculture.